instance fidelity_and_validity_considerations : DTDFVocab:FidelityConsideration [
    base:desc "Model fidelity is maintained by systematically validating and verifying model transformations, for example from SysML specifications to simulation models such as Simulink, as highlighted in the reference literature. Traceability of data traces to their originating processing components and models provides a basis for error detection and correction, ensuring that uncertainties introduced by model conversion or data processing are quantifiable. The approach emphasises real‑time requirements and control‑system dead‑time considerations, requiring that friction models remain accurate throughout the robot’s operational life. Continuous data streams enable dynamic adaptation of both white‑box and black‑box models, supporting ongoing validation against observed behaviour. Quality assurance processes include the verification of correctness of transformations, maintenance of traceability links, and periodic re‑training or re‑parameterisation of models to mitigate drift and maintain the prescribed level of model accuracy."
]

